{"word":"ἡνιοχέω","slug":"ἡνιοχέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἡνιοχέω</b></el> <el>(ἡνιοχέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>prose form of <a href='S:ἡνιοχεύω'><el>ἡνιοχεύω</el></a>,\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to hold the reins</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to drive, guide</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to direct</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be guided</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}